The paper presents a deep convolutional neural network architecture for semantic pixel-wise segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the trade-off between memory and accuracy, which is a common concern in machine learning (cs.LG). The architecture is designed to be efficient and practical, which suggests a focus on applied research (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of trainable filters, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper provides a Caffe implementation and a web demo, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM).
